🧠 3546. Equal Sum Grid Partition I — Notes
🔹 Problem Essence

You are given a grid → need to check:

👉 Can we make ONE cut (horizontal OR vertical)
👉 Such that both parts:

are non-empty
have equal sum
🔹 Key Observations
1. Total Sum Insight
Let total sum = S
For equal partition → each part must be S / 2

👉 If S is odd → impossible immediately

2. Only Straight Cuts Allowed

You are NOT allowed arbitrary partitioning.

Only:

Horizontal cut → between rows
Vertical cut → between columns
🔹 Core Idea

We simulate both possibilities:

🟦 Horizontal Cut
Keep adding rows from top
After each row → check if sum == target

👉 Cut is between row i and i+1

⚠️ Only go till m-1 (so both parts non-empty)

🟩 Vertical Cut
Keep adding columns from left
After each column → check if sum == target

👉 Cut is between col j and j+1

⚠️ Only go till n-1

🔹 Algorithm
Step 1: Compute Total Sum
long long total = 0;
for each cell → add
Step 2: Check feasibility
if (total % 2 != 0) return false;
target = total / 2;
Step 3: Try Horizontal Cuts
sum = 0
for i in [0 → m-2]:
    add entire row i to sum
    if sum == target → return true
Step 4: Try Vertical Cuts
sum = 0
for j in [0 → n-2]:
    add entire column j to sum
    if sum == target → return true
Step 5: If nothing works
return false;
🔹 Complexity
Total cells ≤ 1e5
Time:
Sum calculation → O(m*n)
Horizontal → O(m*n)
Vertical → O(m*n)

👉 Overall: O(m*n)

Space:
O(1) (no extra structures)
🔹 Why This Works (Important Insight ⚡)

Instead of checking all partitions:

We only check prefix sums of rows/columns

👉 Because any valid cut must be:

continuous top/bottom OR left/right
🔹 Edge Cases

✔️ Single row → only vertical cut possible
✔️ Single column → only horizontal cut possible
✔️ Minimum grid (2 cells) → still works
✔️ Large values → use long long

🔹 Pattern Recognition (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)

This is a classic:

✅ Prefix Sum + Partition Check

Whenever you see:

“cut into two equal parts”
“continuous split”
“grid or array”

👉 Think:

Total sum
Prefix accumulation
Compare with target
🔹 Code Intuition Summary
First ensure equal partition possible
Then simulate cuts
Stop early if found
🔹 Mistakes to Avoid ❌
Forgetting m-1 / n-1 limit → leads to empty partition
Using int instead of long long
Recomputing sums repeatedly (inefficient)
